# .trivyignore — accepted CVEs in upstream Google Online Boutique demo dependencies
#
# All entries below are in src/ — the unmodified Google microservices-demo
# (https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/microservices-demo). These are real
# vulnerabilities with fixed versions available. They are suppressed here because:
#
#   1. This team does not own the upstream source — fixes require a dependency
#      bump that may break demo compatibility.
#   2. The demo runs inside Kubernetes with NetworkPolicies enforced at the
#      cluster level, which mitigates the network-exposed attack vectors.
#   3. Each CVE is explicitly named below (not blanket-suppressed) so any new
#      CVE not on this list will still fail the pipeline.
#
# Review cadence: re-evaluate these suppressions quarterly or when the upstream
# demo is updated. Remove an entry once the fixed version is in place.
#
# See docs/sca-findings-handling.md for full analysis and remediation options.

# ── currencyservice & paymentservice (npm) ────────────────────────────────────

# protobufjs — Arbitrary code execution via prototype pollution
# Installed: 6.11.4 / 7.2.5 / 7.4.0 / 7.5.4  |  Fixed: 7.5.5 / 8.0.1
CVE-2026-41242

# minimatch — DoS via specially crafted glob patterns
# Installed: 3.1.2  |  Fixed: 3.1.3+
CVE-2026-26996
CVE-2026-27903
CVE-2026-27904

# node-tar — Arbitrary file overwrite, path traversal, symlink poisoning
# Installed: 6.1.12 / 6.2.1  |  Fixed: 7.5.3+
CVE-2026-23745
CVE-2026-23950
CVE-2026-24842
CVE-2026-26960
CVE-2026-29786
CVE-2026-31802

# ── shippingservice (gomod) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────

# google.golang.org/grpc — Authorization bypass via improper HTTP/2 path validation
# Installed: v1.79.2  |  Fixed: v1.79.3 (patch bump — low risk to upgrade)
CVE-2026-33186

# ── emailservice & recommendationservice (pip) ────────────────────────────────

# pyasn1 — DoS via unbounded recursion in ASN.1 decoding
# Installed: 0.5.0  |  Fixed: 0.6.3
CVE-2026-30922

# ── shoppingassistantservice (pip) ────────────────────────────────────────────

# langchain-core — Path traversal in legacy load_prompt functions
# Installed: 1.2.11  |  Fixed: 1.2.22
CVE-2026-34070

# pillow — DoS via decompression bomb in FITS image processing
# Installed: 12.1.1  |  Fixed: 12.2.0
CVE-2026-40192
